The paper deals with the problem of detecting malware using domain generation algorithms (DGAs) and proposes a machine learning-based approach using long short-term memory (LSTM) networks. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of DNS queries to detect DGAs, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper provides code snippets and experiments with open datasets, indicating a software engineering (cs.SE) aspect to the work.
